<paragraph blockId="22.[192,1440,1665,1928]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,338,1665,1689]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus to 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1937" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1937" box="[554,804,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Tsitana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[554,649,1666,1689]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Tsitana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[655,804,1665,1689]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" refId="ref27329" refString="Evans, W. H. 1937. A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History); London. xii + 212 p., 30 pl." type="book" year="1937">Evans, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[819,873,1665,1689]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Trimen, 1870" authorityName="Trimen" authorityYear="1870" box="[972,1333,1665,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Cyclopides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsita">
<emphasis box="[972,1162,1665,1689]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Cyclopides tsita</emphasis>
Trimen, 1870
</taxonomicName>
) and not monophyletic with 
<taxonomicName authority="Watson, 1893" authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1893" box="[431,713,1699,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Kedestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[431,535,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Kedestes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, E. Y." box="[544,713,1700,1724]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" pagination="3 - 132" part="1893" refId="ref28686" refString="Watson, E. Y. 1893. A proposed classification of the Hesperiidae, with a revision of the genera. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London 1893 (1): 3 - 132." title="A proposed classification of the Hesperiidae, with a revision of the genera" type="journal article" year="1893">Watson, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[730,784,1700,1724]" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Wallengren, 1857" authorityName="Wallengren" authorityYear="1857" box="[889,1342,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Hesperia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepenula">
<emphasis box="[889,1111,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Hesperia lepenula</emphasis>
Wallengren, 1857
</taxonomicName>
), where it was previously placed (
<figureCitation box="[497,567,1734,1758]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="22.[192,275,1419,1441]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,215,1384]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,213,1385]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 9. Genomic trees of Astictopterini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677253/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1793" box="[589,774,1734,1758]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Kedestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nerva">Kedestes nerva</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Hancock and Gardiner" box="[865,1207,1734,1758]" firstAuthor="Hancock" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" pagination="105 - 123" refId="ref27684" refString="Hancock, D. L., and A. J. Gardiner. 1982. The Kedestes nerva group of species (Lepidoptera: Hesperiidae). Arnoldia Zimbabwe 9 (8): 105 - 123." type="journal article" year="1982">Hancock and Gardiner 1982</bibRefCitation>
), keys to V.27.A. in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[192,351,1768,1792]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" refId="ref27329" refString="Evans, W. H. 1937. A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History); London. xii + 212 p., 30 pl." type="book" year="1937">Evans (1937)</bibRefCitation>
. Distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1893" box="[596,697,1767,1791]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Kedestes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[596,697,1767,1791]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="21">Kedestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by mostly dark below antennae (not pale or checkered), orange submarginal markings on forewing above (at least in females), rusty ventral hindwing margin, narrow uncus, upturned almost rectangular harpe with serrated dorsal edge, not separated from ampulla. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly6841.65.2:C1166G, aly2578.13.2:C1091A, aly127.64.1:A1342T, aly83.5.1:A418C, aly904.15.14:C3808G.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="22" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[192,1440,217,242]" box="[192,1440,217,242]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,343,217,241]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, formed from the 
<typeStatus box="[1219,1271,218,242]" pageId="23" pageNumber="22">type</typeStatus>
species name.
</paragraph>
